sheet_summary_5_sentences: The Axial sheet is a glulam column design worksheet that evaluates axial load, bending moment, and combined axial–bending checks for a single member. Users enter geometry, tributary loading, material grade/species, service condition, and stability factors, and the sheet computes factored actions and section properties. The worksheet then derives material modification factors and resistances (compression, tension, moment) consistent with CSA O86 design procedures for glulam members. Finally, it calculates interaction/utilization ratios (e.g., axial/bending utilization) to indicate pass/fail against the standard ≤1.0 acceptance criterion. This sheet should be used during preliminary and detailed design to quickly verify whether a proposed glulam column size and bracing arrangement satisfies code-based resistance requirements.
